Example: Remove All Adjacent Duplicates In String https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-all-adjacent-duplicates-in-string/description/
Code:
class Solution:
    def removeDuplicates(self, s: str) -> str:
        res=[]
        for i in s:
            if len(res)>0 and res[-1]==i:  #If the stack is not empty and the last character equals the current one a, we have an adjacent duplicate.
                res.pop() #remove the last character (duplicate pair is removed).
            else:
                res.append(i) 
        return "".join(res) #"".join(ans) converts it back to a string.


        
